.TH ROSIE 1
.SH NAME
rosie \- generate shell commands from natural-language prompts
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rosie
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIPROMPT\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rosie
takes a natural-language task description, sends it to an OpenAI-compatible
chat completion endpoint, and returns the resulting shell command.
.PP
Prompts can be passed as trailing arguments or via standard input. In an
interactive terminal, Rosie offers to execute the generated command, re-enter
the prompt, or quit after showing the result.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-configure
Interactively create or update the local configuration file.
.TP
.B \-\-install
Install the current binary into the local bin directory and install this man
page into the local man directory when available.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print help information.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Rosie reads configuration in this order:
.IP "1." 4
Environment variables
.IP "2." 4
Local config file at
.I ~/.config/rosie/config.toml
.IP "3." 4
Built-in defaults
.PP
Recognized environment variables:
.TP
.B OPENAI_API_KEY
API key for the OpenAI-compatible endpoint.
.TP
.B OPENAI_ENDPOINT
Base endpoint URL. Defaults to
.I https://api.openai.com
.
.TP
.B OPENAI_MODEL
Model name. Defaults to
.I gpt-4o-mini
.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/rosie/config.toml
Persistent local configuration written by
.BR rosie " " \-\-configure .
.TP
.I ~/.local/bin/rosie
Default install location for the executable when
.B XDG_BIN_HOME
is unset.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/man/man1/rosie.1
Default install location for the man page when
.B XDG_DATA_HOME
is unset.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Configure Rosie:
.B rosie \-\-configure
.TP
Install Rosie:
.B rosie \-\-install
.TP
Generate a command from arguments:
.B rosie show me the top 10 processes by memory usage
.TP
Generate and then choose whether to execute interactively:
.B rosie list open ports
.TP
Generate a command from standard input:
.B echo "list all git branches" | rosie
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B rosie
exits with status 0 on success and non-zero on error.
